  "prompt": "What is a good way to estimate the cost of construction for a residential house in Hyderabad, India?",
  "response": "To estimate the construction cost of a residential house in Hyderabad, India, consider these methods:\n\n1. Per Square Foot Estimation\n- Average construction cost ranges from \u20b91,500 to \u20b95,000 per square foot\n- Depends on quality of materials, design complexity, and location\n- Basic construction: \u20b91,500-\u20b92,500/sq.ft\n- Mid-range construction: \u20b92,500-\u20b93,500/sq.ft\n- Luxury construction: \u20b93,500-\u20b95,000/sq.ft\n\n2. Key Cost Factors\n- Land cost\n- Construction materials\n- Labor charges\n- Design complexity\n- Location within Hyderabad\n- Quality of finishes\n- Architectural design\n\n3. Recommended Estimation Approaches\n- Consult local architects\n- Get quotes from multiple contractors\n- Use online construction cost calculators\n- Check recent construction projects in similar areas\n\n4. Additional Cost Considerations\n- Foundation work\n- Plumbing and electrical systems\n- Interior and exterior finishes\n- Permits and approvals\n- Site preparation\n\n5. Typical Cost Breakdown\n- Land: 30-40% of total project cost\n- Construction: 50-60% of total project cost\n- Miscellaneous expenses: 10-15%\n\nConsulting local professionals will provide the most accurate estimate.",
